### Resource Hinting

* same domain css,js
* cross domain css,js,fonts
* load image after API response
* fonts from css file

1. - preconnect (connect to specific cross origin server in advance) - to avoid making connections again and again
eg. <link rel="preconnect" href="https://cdn.glitch.global"/>
* [performance resource hints](https://learn-performance-resource-hints.glitch.me/1)
1. dns-prefetch (does DNS lookup in advance)
eg. <link rel="dns-prefetch"
      href="https://fonts.gstatic.com">
1. preload(initiate early request to resource for rendering the page)
eg. <link rel="preload"
      href="https://font.woff2" as="font" crossorigin>
* when parsing of HTML is going on pre-hints happen in parallel
1. prefetch(load resources which are needed in near future with low priority -future navigation)
eg. <link rel= "prefetch" href="/next-page.css" as="style">

1. prerender (loads entire page and all its dependency in background which display hidden)
eg. <link rel="pretendeer" href="blog.html">

### Resource Hint Priority
`<!-- Lower priority only for nob-critical preloaded scripts-->
<link rel="preload" href="critical-script.js" as= "script" >
<link rel="preload" href="/js/script.js" as= "script" fetchpriority="low">
<!-- Preload CSS without blocking other resources-->
<link rel="preload" as="style" href="theme.css" fetchpriority="low" onload="this.rel='stylesheet">
`
* preload is just going to download. to render is needs relation as stylesheet
[fetch priority](https://web.dev/articles/fetch-priority)

